  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bangladesh: National Human Rights Commission Capacity Development Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. To monitor, investigate and report on serious human rights violations; 2. To engage and follow-up with select UN human rights treaty bodies; and 3. To advocate for law reform on certain issues within the BNHRC&#x2019;s mandate.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct: Leadership and staff of the BNHRC; Indirect: Victims of human rights violations in Bangladesh, especially those most vulnerable, entitled to assistance from the BNHRC.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to address serious human rights violations in Bangladesh by providing capacity building and technical assistance support to strengthen the capacity of the Bangladesh National Human Rights Commission (BNHRC).</narrative>
  </description>
